  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [X] Foundry\r\n- [X] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\nforge 0.2.0 (cd7850b 2023-02-02T00:05:14.844624Z)\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\nforge test\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\nmacOS (Apple Silicon)\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nStart with any Foundry project with invariant tests, e.g. https://github.com/lucas-manuel/invariant-examples, and set the following configuration:\r\n\r\n```toml\r\n[profile.default]\r\n  fuzz = { runs = 1_000 }\r\n\r\n[profile.default.invariant]\r\n  call_override = false\r\n  fail_on_revert = true\r\n  depth = 100\r\n\r\n# Speed up compilation and tests during development\r\n[profile.lite]\r\n  fuzz = { runs = 50 }\r\n  optimizer = false\r\n```\r\n\r\nThen, run the invariants like this:\r\n\r\n```sh\r\nFOUNDRY_PROFILE=lite forge test --mt \"invariant_\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nYou will notice that the number of runs for the invariant tests is 256, and not 50, as one would expect by reading the [Foundry Book](https://book.getfoundry.sh/reference/config/testing#invariant):\r\n\r\n> If the common entries are not set in the `[invariant]` section, but are set in the `[fuzz]` (same as `[profile.default.fuzz]`) section, then the values from the `[fuzz]` section will be used.\r\n\r\nThat is, in the config above the `fuzz.runs` is set to 50, but the invariant test don't use it. Instead, the default number of runs of 256 is applied. This can also be seen by running `forge config`.",
